{{partial 'otherHeader'}}

{{outlet}}
<div class="row">
  <div class="two columns"> </div>
  <div class="eight columns">
  <h3>Create New Post</h3>
  <p>Creating a Flowerpot posts hides potentially upsetting content, making sure
    that those potentially upset by the content won't read it by accident. You
    can see an example {{link-to "here" 'post' 'example'}}.</p>

    <p>You write a warning note for each post describing why the content might be
    upsetting, and readers consent to reading by clicking the 'Display' button
    on your post! Please keep your title neutral.</p>

    <form id="new-post-form">
  <label>Post Title:</label>
  {{input class='title' value=model.title}}

  <label>Warning: <span>(be specific, so that readers know why
    the content is potentially upsetting)</span></label>
  {{textarea class='note' value=model.note}}

  <label>Content:</label>
  {{textarea class='content' value=model.content}}

  <button class="submit button create-new" {{action 'submitTheThing' model}}>Create</button>
</form>
  </div>
  <div class="two columns"></div>
</div>
